  "Static friction from the ice surface": "",
  "There is no friction on ice at all": "",
  "Kinetic friction from the ice surface": "",
  "Gravitational friction from the Earth": "",
  "The puck is sliding, so kinetic friction acts on it. Even though ice is very smooth with low friction, there is still some kinetic friction that gradually slows the puck down over time.": "",
  "Why do car tires have treads (grooves) on them?": "",
  "To make the car look more attractive and stylish": "",
  "To reduce friction so the car goes faster always": "",
  "To increase friction and channel away water for grip": "",
  "To make the tires weigh less overall for the car": "",
